Class ThreadedCommand

java.lang.Object
frc.team5431.titan.core.robot.ThreadedCommand
All Implemented Interfaces:
edu.wpi.first.wpilibj2.command.Command
@Deprecated public class ThreadedCommand extends Object implements edu.wpi.first.wpilibj2.command.Command
Deprecated.
This is a bad idea; alternatively, look at https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/convenience-features/scheduling-functions.html
This class will allow you to wrap a command inside a seperate thread and still act as a command

  • Constructor Details

    • ThreadedCommand

      public ThreadedCommand(edu.wpi.first.wpilibj2.command.CommandBase baseCommand, double period)
      Deprecated.
      Creates A threaded command that will call a specified command at a different rate than the command scheduler would normally allow.
      Parameters:
      baseCommand - the command that will be running in a seperate thread
      period - period of time between the execute calls. If zero, then the command will be ran as fast as possible
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - thrown when the period is less than zero
      NullPointerException - thrown if the base command or period is null
